The evidence with the title 'Losing ground: Southeast Louisiana is disappearing, quickly ... ' says Aug 28, 2014  ... The landscape on which all that is built is washing away at arate of a football field every hour , 16 square miles per year . For years, most residents didn't notice because they live inside the levees and seldom travel into the wetlands . But even those who work or play in the marshes were misled for decades  ... 
